---
import PageLayout from '@/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import siteConfig from '@/config/site.config';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Docs"
  description="Documentation for VMFlux OBJ Exporter: installation, usage, export options, output files, and troubleshooting."
>
  <section class="border-b border-border bg-background">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-16 lg:px-8">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">Docs</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
        VMFlux OBJ Exporter documentation
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg text-foreground-muted">
        Setup, usage, export options, output files, and troubleshooting for the current
        VMFlux exporter. This page is also suitable to become the future F1 help target.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a
          href={siteConfig.appStoreUrl}
          class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-[#f15a24] px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm transition hover:bg-[#d94d1c]"
        >
          View on Autodesk App Store
        </a>

        <a
          href={`mailto:${siteConfig.email}`}
          class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-border px-5 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-foreground transition hover:bg-muted"
        >
          Contact support
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="border-b border-border bg-muted/30">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-5 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid gap-4 text-sm font-medium text-foreground md:grid-cols-4">
        <div>Supports Navisworks 2024 / 2025 / 2026</div>
        <div>Exports OBJ + MTL</div>
        <div>Scope and units controls included</div>
        <div>Support by email</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-background">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-16 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[0.75fr_1.25fr]">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">
            Quick navigation
          </p>
          <div class="mt-6 rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-foreground-muted">
              <li><a href="#overview" class="hover:text-foreground">Overview</a></li>
              <li><a href="#supported-versions" class="hover:text-foreground">Supported versions</a></li>
              <li><a href="#installation" class="hover:text-foreground">Installation</a></li>
              <li><a href="#how-to-open" class="hover:text-foreground">How to open the exporter</a></li>
              <li><a href="#export-options" class="hover:text-foreground">Export options</a></li>
              <li><a href="#output-files" class="hover:text-foreground">Output files</a></li>
              <li><a href="#troubleshooting" class="hover:text-foreground">Troubleshooting</a></li>
              <li><a href="#support" class="hover:text-foreground">Support</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-12">
          <section id="overview">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">Overview</p>
            <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
              What the exporter does
            </h2>
            <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
              <p>
                VMFlux OBJ Exporter converts supported Navisworks model content into
                <span class="font-medium text-foreground"> OBJ + MTL </span>
                output for downstream workflows such as visualization, review, conversion,
                and external handoff.
              </p>
              <p>
                The exporter is designed for practical project use and includes export scope
                control, units selection, and material-aware output behavior.
              </p>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section id="supported-versions">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">Compatibility</p>
            <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
              Supported versions
            </h2>
            <div class="mt-6 rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
              <ul class="space-y-3 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
                <li>Navisworks 2024</li>
                <li>Navisworks 2025</li>
                <li>Navisworks 2026</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section id="installation">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">Installation</p>
            <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
              How to install
            </h2>
            <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
              <p>
                Installation and updates are handled through the Autodesk App Store package
                for the exporter.
              </p>
              <ol class="space-y-2 pl-5">
                <li>1. Go to the Autodesk App Store listing for VMFlux OBJ Exporter.</li>
                <li>2. Download and install the package for your Navisworks version.</li>
                <li>3. Open Navisworks after installation completes.</li>
                <li>4. Launch the exporter from the VMFlux command or ribbon location in Navisworks.</li>
              </ol>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section id="how-to-open">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">Usage</p>
            <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
              How to open the exporter
            </h2>
            <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
              <p>Open Navisworks, then launch the VMFlux exporter from its installed UI entry.</p>
              <p>
                Once opened, the exporter dialog lets you choose export scope, units, and
                whether to preserve numeric values without unit scaling.
              </p>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section id="export-options">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">Export options</p>
            <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
              What each option means
            </h2>

            <div class="mt-8 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Export scope</h3>
                <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
                  <p>
                    <span class="font-medium text-foreground">Selected Models</span> exports
                    only the currently selected model items.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    <span class="font-medium text-foreground">Entire Model</span> exports the
                    whole model available in the current Navisworks file.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Units</h3>
                <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
                  <p>The exporter supports these output units:</p>
                  <p>mm, cm, m, km, in, ft, yd, mi</p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6 md:col-span-2">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Keep numeric values (no unit scaling)</h3>
                <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
                  <p>
                    When this option is enabled, the exporter keeps the original numeric values
                    instead of scaling them to match the selected output unit.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    This can be useful when the downstream tool or workflow expects the original
                    coordinate magnitudes to remain unchanged.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section id="output-files">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">Output</p>
            <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
              Files generated by export
            </h2>

            <div class="mt-8 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">OBJ</h3>
                <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
                  The main geometry file containing exported mesh data.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">MTL</h3>
                <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
                  The material definition file associated with the OBJ export.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-8 rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Material behavior</h3>
              <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
                <p>
                  The exporter includes material-aware output with real Navisworks material naming
                  and transparency handling for more useful downstream results.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Output organization is designed to be practical for real project workflows,
                  including per-instance group structure where applicable.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section id="troubleshooting">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">Troubleshooting</p>
            <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
              Common issues
            </h2>

            <div class="mt-8 space-y-6">
              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Exporter does not open</h3>
                <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
                  Confirm that the correct plugin version is installed for your Navisworks version,
                  then restart Navisworks and try again.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Export result is incomplete</h3>
                <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
                  Check whether you exported <span class="font-medium text-foreground">Selected Models</span>
                  instead of <span class="font-medium text-foreground">Entire Model</span>, or retry with a
                  smaller subset to isolate the issue.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Units look wrong downstream</h3>
                <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
                  Re-check the selected output unit and whether
                  <span class="font-medium text-foreground"> Keep numeric values (no unit scaling) </span>
                  was enabled.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-6">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Cannot write export files</h3>
                <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
                  Make sure the destination folder is writable and not blocked by permissions,
                  sync software, or security controls.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section id="support">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-600">Support</p>
            <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">
              Need help?
            </h2>
            <div class="mt-6 rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
              <p class="text-base leading-7 text-foreground-muted">
                Support is currently handled by email. Include your Navisworks version,
                what you were exporting, and what happened so the issue can be reviewed faster.
              </p>
              <p class="mt-6">
                <a
                  href={`mailto:${siteConfig.email}`}
                  class="text-base font-medium text-foreground hover:underline"
                >
                  {siteConfig.email}
                </a>
              </p>
            </div>
          </section>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>